<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-16T11:48:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-16T11:48:00-05:00" n="964" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d964">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 714.1515/28</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Ewing</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-16T11:00:00-05:48">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s November 12, 5 p.m. Government replies accepting offer
                            United States to mediate boundary dispute with Guatemala. This request
                            for mediation originally suggested by Honduras to United States March 5
                            last. Honduras denies presence of troops numbering neighborhood
                            thousand, ordinarily maintaining only twenty-nine soldiers this district
                            with additional twenty at present.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ewing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>